      "writtenOn": "2017-11-09T21:57:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If you do keep the tag, you can do this in one line, I think, given that your code never needs to see the definition of the struct you\u0027re using as a tag.  You can just shove the declaration into the template arguments...\n\n#define SK_MAKE_NAMED_BOOL(NAME) \\\n    using NAME \u003d SkTNamedBool\u003cstruct SkTNamedBool_NAME_##NAME\u003e\n\n(Pretty sure)",
      "revId": "20b0a6cd5ff368cc88c4fabf19dc810a6f5539f5",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
