    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ec0c177f_d4629c8d",
        "filename": "include/core/SkTypes.h",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 463,
      "author": {
        "id": 5633
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-09T22:08:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That would compile, however I think the struct is given global scope, meaning:\n\nclass Class1 {\n    SK_MAKE_NAMED_BOOL(SomeBool);\n};\n\nclass Class2 {\n    SK_MAKE_NAMED_BOOL(SomeBool);\n};\n\nClass1::SomeBool and Class2::SomeBool are the same type now and interchangeable.\n\nI can\u0027t think of a reason why not to just declare the struct at the correct scope though instead of putting in a definition.\n\n struct SkTNamedBool_NAME_##NAME;\n using NAME \u003d SkTNamedBool\u003cSkTNamedBool_NAME_##NAME\u003e;",
      "parentUuid": "fb4ecb7c_1422b5a7",
